<|startoftext|>I've had this home for 5 or 10 years now, but recently I decided to move out of this lease, so I could really take care of myself and my new roommate. I called them first thing on January 1nd, 2017, and made sure to ask about a 3 month deposit. I asked about a 3 month sublease since my daughter lived together with me for her first 6 months in the apartment, and there was a little hesitation about putting her in the apartment. When I first called they just made me feel like I didn't understand. I explained that my daughter and my daughter lived in the apartment, and that the first month I was leasing out my daughter would usually be her first month, but they assured me it wouldn't be the last. They said there were several fees the landlord incurred in regards to this one, but I explained to them they just said they had to pay the fees out of an account. They said it was not their problem they would just have to give the money out of their accounts. I went into the account after explaining what was going on and they told me it was just a misunderstanding and that their employee was just explaining it. I explained to them about the deposit, then they said they would try to get me back. When I went to pick him up, this time I asked about the 3 month deposit as well. They said no, they did not have to pay it out of the account. I explained to them that just because they don't have a deposit it doesn't mean they have to pay it out! They kept pushing me back saying they didn't have a deposit! I went home with it, after explaining it. I picked it up, and explained it to them! They looked at it and then said to me, oh well they don't accept deposits this week. What?! And I went on an explain I didn't want a deposit, and then explained to them that this wasn't my daughter's last month. Just because it was my daughter's first month would mean she didn't get an account to stay in. They finally gave me back my deposit! Not only did they don't give me back my deposit, they didn't want to get me out! I'm leaving this here.  Anyways, this is my 3 years old's first visit to the school she was supposed to go to, she's not here! Oh my goodness. This just ruined their business! They're no longer treating their customers right! I'm from out of town now and I'll be considering going to the school in the future. Thanks!<|endoftext|>
